{"lemma":"كُرْسِيٌّ","slug":"كُرْسِيٌّ","root":"ك.ر.س.#","root_slug":"ك-ر-س-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ك-ر-س-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"كُرْسِيّ","root":"كرس","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n36881"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%83%D9%8F%D8%B1%D9%92%D8%B3%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%8C%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"chair, seat"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"seating"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"throne","examples":[{"text":"وَسِعَ كُرْسِيُّهُ ٱلسَّمَاوَاتِ وَٱلْأَرْضَ","english":"His throne extends over the heavens and the earth"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"capital of a column, chapiter","tags":["alt-of","uppercase"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"chair for lectures, lectern, pulpit, cathedra, a kind of desk upon which a document is placed"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pillar of a bridge"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"gun carriage, the mounting of a mangonel"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Etymology tree\nAramaic כּוּרְסְיָא (kursəyā)bor.\nClassical Syriac ܟܘܪܣܝܐ (kursəyā)bor.\nArabic كرسي\nDeemed with such a shape borrowed from Aramaic כּוּרְסְיָא / ܟܘܪܣܝܐ (kursəyā). Compare Biblical Hebrew כִּסֵּא (kisséʔ), Ugaritic 𐎋𐎒𐎜 (ksủ /⁠kussīʾu⁠/) and Akkadian 𒄑𒄖𒍝 (kussûm). Ultimately from Sumerian 𒄑𒄖𒍝 (^(g̃eš)gu-za /⁠guza⁠/, “chair”)."},"ipa":["/kur.sijj/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n36881","headword_ar":"كُرْسِىٌّ","root":"krs","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and (sometimes, S, Msb)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kirosiY~N","text_ar":"كِرْسِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A throne;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sariyrN","text_ar":"سَرِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a chair:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TK:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a seat not larger than is sufficient for one person:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd, ii. 256:) [and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a stool:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"karaAsiY~N","text_ar":"كَرَاسِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and sometimes"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"karaAsK","text_ar":"كَرَاسٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", agreeably with a rule mentioned by ISk. (Msb.) It is the place [or seat] of the king, and of the learned man: and hence, as used in the Kur ii. 256, it is explained as signifying (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Dominion:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) and (tropical:)  the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"power"},{"kind":"text","text":"of God, whereby He holds the heavens and the earth: (TA:) and (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knowledge:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K:) which last explanation is ascribed to I'Ab: but the truth is, that I'Ab explained it as there signifying the ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"foot-stool"},{"kind":"text","text":"of God; or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place of the feet:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but as to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Earo$","text_ar":"عَرْش"},{"kind":"text","text":"[of God], this is immeasurable: (Az, TA:) or it signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sphere of the stars."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Er$","text_ar":"عرش"},{"kind":"text","text":".) [Hence,"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2606},{"kind":"text","text":"also, you say,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa mino A^aholi AlkurosiY~i","text_ar":"هُوَ مِنْ اَهْلِ الكُرْسِىِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is of the people of science."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TK.) [And hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlkaraAsiY~u","text_ar":"الكَرَاسِىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also used [elliptically] to signify (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The learned men;"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to Ktr. (A.) ―         -b2-  Also,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A prop,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"support,"},{"kind":"text","text":"for a wall. (TA.) ―         -b3-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aAtu AlkurosiY~i","text_ar":"ذَاتُ الكُرْسِىِّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Constellation Cassiopeia:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaDiybN","text_ar":"خَضِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TK","A","TA","Az"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}